22
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:34,000
And I began to have nightmares of Rwanda.

23
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:44,000
And of course at that stage, you know, it was obvious that I was traumatized, but again, did I got a psychiatrist?

24
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:48,000
No, I didn't. I kept doing the job.

25
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:50,000
Did you turn to other things?

26
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:51,000
Boos.

27
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:53,000
Boos. I mean how much booze are we talking?

28
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:56,000
You know, the truth is I was in an alcoholic language before I got to Rwanda.

29
00:02:56,000 --> 00:03:03,000
But I was in the kind of functioning alcoholic, what they call, you know, managing it, stage of the disease.

30
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:10,000
When Furgle returned home from Rwanda, he started having nightmares, obsessing and frightening dreams.

31
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:21,000
